Ogunleye will let his playdecide
Defensive lineman would like to finish career as aBear
Updated: October 7, 2009, 1:31 AM ET
By Jeff Dickerson 
With 4.5 sacks in just four games, Bears defensive end Adewale Ogunleye is making a strong case for a contract extension, with the deal he signed back on Aug. 21, 2004, set to expire after this season.
Ogunleye talked about the possibility of finishing his career in a Bears uniform during an appearance Tuesday on ESPN 1000's "Football Night in Chicago."
"I love Chicago," Ogunleye said. "Coming here from Miami was a tough trade ...
